caption:
&quot;As part of our Earth Month programming, we hosted our Earth Month Arts Festival where students were able to explore activities inside and outside of the gallery. 🎨🌎

Outside the gallery, we had a scavenger hunt where students had the opportunity to learn more about the Latino Cultural Center as they completed trivia questions. Our winners received a couple of goodies such as a pot with seeds and a tea mix from the @uichertiagegardern, stickers, pins, and a crocheted plush of our LCC mascot, Pilar made by @crochetsbymonse. 🐛🐛

Along with the scavenger hunt, there were many other activities that students were able to participate in such as making buttons, chalk art, screen printing with @marimachamonarcapress, the @uiclibrary pop-up library, take a nice photo with our photo-booth backdrop made by @magdadoesart with props from @artistic_disasters and getting a free cup of coffee from @anticonquiestacafe ☕📚

Inside the gallery students had the opportunity to get a snack, look through the LCC archives learn about our rich history, and meet some of the local environmental community organizations such as:
@pcrchi
@n4ejchicago
@pilsen_perro
 @chicago_chrp
@sustainableuic 
@lvejo20 
 @uicheritagegarden

Thank you to everyone who stopped by and made this such a successful program! We had an awesome turnout, seeing familiar and new faces! Thank you to all our collaborators and community members for making this event possible! Make sure to check them out and show support ❤️ We still have our LCC Snack Bags going on the rest of this week to help students fuel up for finals!&quot;.

